ex certificated linen clothing with plastic free packaging.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Clothing</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.lovelinen.com.au/\">Love Linen</a> - Linen clothing made with love in Australia</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Clothing</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.nn07.com/\">NN07</a> - Using its <a href=\"https://www.nn07.com/made-to-last\">sustainable material matrix</a>, No Nationality designs made-to-last clothing primarily with recycled and non-cotton natural materials including hemp, linen, wool, alpaca, and silk.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Clothing</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.sustainablehosiery.com/\">Sustainable Hosiery</a> - OEKO-TEX certified, vegan-dyed hosiery made from 76% - 97% recycled post-production and post-consumer nylon waste in Zero Waste factories</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Clothing</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.woronstore.com/\">Woron Store</a> - Lingerie and base wear essentials made from GOTS-certified, antibacterial 'Lenzing Modal' (Beech wood!) made from CO2-neutral FSC-certified native tree plantations.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Documentaries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.greenfund.org/en/m61.php\">Green Film Festival in Seoul</a> - Starting with Green Film Festival in Seoul in 2004, Korea Green Foundation has been seeking ways of coexistence of the environment and humans and has been exploring the alternatives and better practice for the future.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Food</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.agricool.co/fr\">Agricool - Local, healthy, sustainable food</a> - Des fruits et légumes, cultivés au coeur des villes, à moins de 15km de leur lieu de consommation. Frais, locaux, sans pesticides.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Food</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.boulderfoodrescue.org/\">Boulder Food Rescue</a> - We facilitate the sustainable redistribution of healthy food that would otherwise be wasted to low-income communities, by bicycle. We work with communities to facilitate their own food redistribution and create decentralized systems to bypass barriers to food access. Our work envisions a world in which everyone has equitable access to healthy food.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Food</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cityharvest.org/\">City Harvest</a> - City Harvest is New York City’s largest food rescue organization. They rescue food and deliver it to hundreds of food pantries, soup kitchens and other community partners.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Food</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.grownyc.org/compost/locations\">GrowNYC Food Scrap Collection Schedule</a> - Interactive map with over 150 residential Food Scrap Drop-Off sites in NYC.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Food</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://karma.life/\">Karma</a> - Rescue unsold meals, delivered, always 50% off in hundreds of cities across Sweden, United Kingdom, and France.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Food</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://new.karma.life/\">Karma</a> - A Swedish company that lets restaurants sell surplus food at a lower price. It lets you pay less for food and prevent food waste.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Food</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://olioex.com/\">Olio</a> - We connect neighbors to share food, and other things, rather than chuck them away.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Food</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.rethinkfood.nyc/\">Rethink Food NYC</a> - They pick up unused, excess food from restaurants, farms, and other food purveyors, and re-purpose it into delicious and nutritious meals for under-served New Yorkers.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Jobs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://techjobsforgood.com/\">Tech Jobs for Good</a> - Find tech jobs at social impact companies, foundations, and innovative nonprofits in the United States. They cover all sorts of impact areas, with Environment being one you can select. Some jobs are remote, some are in-office.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Reforestation</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://coforest.co.uk/\">Coforest</a> - To create our first co-forest in the Bath &#x26; Bristol area, we’re inviting organisations and individuals to adopt up to an acre of land. You’ll be able to name your forest plot and even help to plant it. Together, we’ll create a whole new forest.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Transportation</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://climatechoice.co/change-how-you-travel\">Change How You Travel from Climate Choice</a> - 26% of the greenhouse gases emitted into our atmosphere are from the production and use of vehicles and airplanes. See what what you can do now, and learn about the benefits of changing your travel.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Travel</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://climatechoice.co/change-how-you-travel\">Change How You Travel from Climate Choice</a> - 26% of the greenhouse gases emitted into our atmosphere are from the production and use of vehicles and airplanes. See what what you can do now, and learn about the benefits of changing your travel.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Travel</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://greentickets.app/\">Green Tickets</a> - Traveling is amazing, right? We completely agree! But you probably know that traveling can have a large climate impact. With Green Tickets you can take responsibility of your travel behaviour and reduce your footprint, while still enjoying everything that traveling has to offer.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Travel</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.thetravelfoundation.org.uk/\">The Travel Foundation</a> - Find hotels here which aren't all plastic all the time, amongst other things. This charity brings together travel businesses, suppliers, community groups, governments, local authorities and more to develop practical solutions which maximise the benefits and minimise the negative impacts of tourism in destinations.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Waste</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.nofoodwasted.com/\">No Food Wasted</a> - NoFoodWasted maps products that reach the best before date and shows where and how much you can save. Download the app, select a provider near you and start saving today.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Waste</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.recyclenow.com/\">Recycle Now</a> - Find out where to recycle pretty much anything, including aerosols, old mobile phones, soft plastics, and get advice on how to reduce waste too.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Waste</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://repaircafe.org/\">Repair Café</a> - Repair Cafés are free meeting places and they’re all about repairing things (together). You’ll find tools and materials to help you make any repairs to clothes, furniture, electrical appliances, bicycles, crockery, appliances, toys, et cetera. You’ll also find expert volunteers, with repair skills in all kinds of fields. Repair your stuff, or just enjoy a coffee. They're world-wide, and the site is multi-lingual.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"philsturgeon/awesome-earth","categoryHTML":"<h2>Waste</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://vegware.co.uk/\">Vegware</a> - Napkins, carrier bags, salad boxes, sushi trays, cutlery, disposable coffee cups, all made from plants using renewable, lower carbon, recycled or reclaimed materials, and designed to be commercially compostable with food waste, where accepted.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-13T14:08:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sindresorhus/awesome-nodejs","categoryHTML":"<h2>Packages</h2><h3>Documentation</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/facebook/docusaurus\">Docusaurus</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/facebook/docusaurus\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 